                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            What are LED light bulbs?
                                        </head_sticky>
                                        <para>Are you still using regular light bulbs at home? </para><br />
                                        <para>
                                            1. Convince your parents to replace them with <bold>LED light bulbs!</bold><br /><br />
                                            2. Eco-friendly LED light bulbs use <bold>far less energy</bold> to produce the same light output.
                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>Does Unplugging really make a Difference?</head_sticky>
                                        <para>
                                            <br />
                                            You won’t notice the impact immediately, but the energy costs of plugged-in appliances can really add up over time.<br /><br />
                                            It is a simple way to help your parents to save 5% to 10% on their electric bill!

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>


                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>What to do Before Touching appliances?</head_sticky>
                                        <para>
                                            <br />
                                            1. Always remember to dry your hands first!

                                            <br /><br />
                                            2. It prevents any chances of electrical shock due to touching them with wet hands.<br />

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>When should I Open/Close the Windows?</head_sticky>
                                        <para>
                                            <br />
                                            1. If there is cool wind outside, close all cooling appliances and open the windows to let fresh air come in. <br />
                                            <br />
                                            2. If you have to switch on cooling appliances because it is too hot outside, close the windows so that your cooling appliances are more efficient.

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>Microwave, Oven or Stove</head_sticky>
                                        <para>
                                            <br />
                                            1. A microwave uses 50% less energy than others if you just want to reheat your food.<br /><br />
                                            2. Use appropriate size for the pan to cook with a stove, as smaller pans are more energy-efficient to heat up.
                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>


                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>Highlight Notes</head_sticky>
                                        <para>
                                            <br />
                                            1. A LED bulb do not emits any polluting radiation, hence switch to them. <br />
                                            2. Unplug all devices from wall when not in use.<br />
                                            3. Dry hands before touching any appliances.<br />
                                            4. Reheat food with microwave.<br />
                                            5. Close window depending on weather outside.
                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <h3 style="color:#000000;font-family:sans-serif"><mybox>Myths about Global Warming</mybox></h3>


                        <div style="margin:auto; padding-top:20px;">
                            <ul>
                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            Is Global Warming not REAL?
                                        </head_sticky><br />
                                        <para>
                                            1. Some people believe that it doesn’t exist or will have no impact on Earth.<br /><br />
                                            2. This is NOT true because the Earth’s average surface temperature has increased.

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            Did HUMANS cause Global Warming?
                                        </head_sticky><br />

                                        <para>
                                            There are people who believe that humans are not responsible for global warming.<br /><br />
                                            This is NOT true because most scientists agree that global warming is mainly caused by humans’ activities.

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            Is Global Warming a FUTURE problem?
                                        </head_sticky><br />
                                        <para>
                                            Some people believe that it is not an issue that we should pay attention now.<br /><br />
                                            This is NOT true because it will be too late if we address this issue later.

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            Can cow FARTS cause Global Warming?
                                        </head_sticky><br />
                                        <para>
                                            It is a myth that cow farts cause global warming.<br /><br />
                                            Regardless it is true or not, humans are still the primary cause of the issue.

                                        </para>

                                    </alpha>
                                </li>

                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
                                            Will animals ADAPT to Global Warming?
                                        </head_sticky><br />
                                        <para>
                                            Animals are used to adapt to new environments or move to a new living place.
                                            <br /><br />
                                            However, it is impossible for animals to adapt quickly enough if the speed of warming is too fast.

                                        </para>
                                    </alpha>
                                </li>


                                <li style="width:30.33%">
                                    <alpha href="#">
                                        <head_sticky>
